          "nodes": [
            {
              "id": "IC_kwDOFcwZ1c6jOjcM",
              "body": "### PR summary [9e66e7c35c](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/23124/commits/9e66e7c35c81a8118f94a75b6a29717db7aee32f)\n\n#### Import changes for modified files\n\nNo significant changes to the import graph\n\n\n<details><summary>Import changes for all files</summary>\n\n|Files|Import difference|\n|-|-|\n| `Mathlib.Topology.MetricSpace.Net` (new file)|1360|\n\n</details>\n\n---\n\n<details><summary>\n\n#### Declarations diff\n\n</summary>\n\n`+ IsNet`\n`+ IsNet.anti`\n`+ IsNet.empty`\n`+ IsNet.isCompact`\n`+ IsNet.isCompact_closure`\n`+ IsNet.mono`\n`+ IsNet.of_maximal_isSeparated`\n`+ IsNet.of_subset_cthickening`\n`+ IsNet.of_subset_cthickening_of_lt`\n`+ IsNet.of_subset_iUnion_closedBall`\n`+ IsNet.subset_cthickening`\n`+ IsNet.subset_iUnion_closedBall`\n`+ exists_finite_isNet_of_isCompact`\n`+ exists_finite_isNet_of_isCompact_closure`\n`+ isCompact_closure_iff_exists_finite_isNet`\n`+ isNet_closure`\n`+ isNet_iff_subset_cthickening`\n`+ isNet_iff_subset_iUnion_closedBall`\n`+ isNet_iff_subset_iUnion_emetricClosedBall`\n`+ isNet_zero`\n`+ ⟨_,`\n<details>\n  <summary>You can run this locally as follows</summary>\n\n\n```bash\n## summary with just the declaration names:\n./scripts/declarations_diff.sh <optional_commit>\n\n## more verbose report:\n./scripts/declarations_diff.sh long <optional_commit>\n```\n</details>\n\nThe doc-module for `script/declarations_diff.sh` contains some details about this script.\n\n</details>\n\n---\n\n<details><summary>No changes to technical debt.</summary>\n\nYou can run this locally as\n```\n./scripts/technical-debt-metrics.sh pr_summary\n```\n* The `relative` value is the weighted *sum* of the differences with weight given by the *inverse* of the current value of the statistic.\n* The `absolute` value is the `relative` value divided by the total sum of the inverses of the current values (i.e. the weighted *average* of the differences).\n</details>\n",
              "createdAt": "2025-03-19T23:23:25Z",
              "author": {
                "login": "github-actions"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "IC_kwDOFcwZ1c6jZvhK",
              "body": "I have an issue of terminology.\r\n\r\n1) The notions you define in this file and *MetricSpace.MetricSeparated* are very close to those defined in *Dynamics.TopologicalEntropy.CoverEntropy* and *Dynamics.TopologicalEntropy.NetEntropy*, with significant mathematical overlap.\r\n\r\n2) Due to point 1), it would be much better to have a common framework for both notions (e.g. defining it on uniform spaces, and specialize to pseudo-emetric spaces).\r\n\r\n3) While point 2) is not exactly urgent, it would be helpful to keep things somewhat coherent between those files. The most annoying issue I see right now is that what you call an *epsilon-net* is called an *epsilon-cover* in the context of dynamical systems, and what you call an *epsilon-separated set* is called an *epsilon-net* in the context of dynamical systems. So we would have two contrary notions of nets in very close contexts.\r\n\r\nThis is an annoying issue about diverging mathematical traditions. Would it be possible to keep the nomenclature coherent (one way or the other) in prevision of a future unification? For instance using e.g. cover/packing ?",
              "createdAt": "2025-03-20T19:13:33Z",
              "author": {
                "login": "D-Thomine"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
